
[1]suburbs

   SUB'URBS, n. [L. suburbium; sub and urbs, a city.]

   1. A building without the walls of a city, but near them; or more
   generally, the parts that lie without the walls, but in the vicinity of
   a city. The word may signify buildings, streets or territory. We say, a
   house stands in the suburbs; a garden is situated in the suburbs of
   London or Paris.

   2. The confines; the out part.

   The suburb of their straw-built citadel.
